OL,3,C400bn euros price tag for united
OL,4,CIreland 'just wrong', expert says
OL,6,FOutlining his main objections, Prof
OL,7,FDoyle said that the IIEA report adds
OL,8,Fmore than 4.2 billion euros to the
OL,9,Fannual cost of unity through
OL,10,Fincreasing public sector wages to
OL,11,FRepublic of Ireland levels.
OL,13,FHowever, he said this made no
OL,14,Fallowance for the taxes (which would
OL,15,Fbe overwhelmingly at the higher rate
OL,16,Fof 40%), PRSI (4%) and pension
OL,17,Fcontributions (expected to be around
OL,18,F10%) to be paid on that increase.
