OL,3,C400bn euros price tag for united
OL,4,CIreland 'just wrong', expert says
OL,6,FProf Doyle's calculations reduce the
OL,7,Freal cost of salary increases by 2.2
OL,8,Fbillion euros annually.
OL,10,FFurthermore, he said it was
OL,11,F"unrealistic and unnecessary" to
OL,12,Fsuggest that public-sector pay would
OL,13,Fimmediately increase to Republic of
OL,14,FIreland levels in year one.
OL,16,F"Merging salary levels over 15 years `
OL,17,Fhalf the time taken by Germany ` would
OL,18,Fmean a cost of approximately 133
OL,19,Fmillion euro in year one, rising on
OL,20,Faverage by that amount each year."
